#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:1
msgid "Feature Name: `cfg_boolean_literals`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:2
msgid "Start Date: 2024-09-16"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:3
msgid ""
"RFC PR: [rust-lang/rfcs#3695](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/3695)"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:4
msgid ""
"Tracking Issue: [rust-lang/rust#131204](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/"
"issues/131204)"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:6
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:9
msgid ""
"Allow `true` and `false` boolean literals as `cfg` predicates, i.e. "
"`cfg(true)`/`cfg(false)`."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:11
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:14
msgid ""
"Often, we may want to temporarily disable a block of code while working on a "
"project; this can be useful, for example, to disable functions which have "
"errors while refactoring a codebase."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:16
msgid ""
"Currently, the easiest ways for programmers to do this are to comment out "
"the code block (which means syntax highlighting no longer works), or to use "
"`cfg(any())` (which is not explicit in meaning)."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:18
msgid ""
"By allowing `#[cfg(false)]`, we can provide programmers with an explicit and "
"more intuitive way to disable code, while retaining IDE functionality."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:20
msgid ""
"Allowing `cfg(true)` would also make temporarily enabling `cfg`'ed out code "
"easier; a `true` may be added to a `cfg(any(..))` list. Adding a "
"`cfg(all())` is the current equivalent of this."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:22
msgid "Guide-level explanation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:25
msgid ""
"Boolean literals (i.e. `true` and `false`) may be used as `cfg` predicates, "
"to evaluate as always true/false respectively."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:27
msgid "Reference-level explanation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:30
msgid ""
"The syntax for configuration predicates should be extended to include "
"boolean literals:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:32
msgid ""
"**<sup>Syntax</sup>**  \n"
"_ConfigurationPredicate_ :  \n"
"      _ConfigurationOption_  \n"
"   | _ConfigurationAll_  \n"
"   | _ConfigurationAny_  \n"
"   | _ConfigurationNot_   \n"
"   | `true` | `false`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:40
msgid "And the line"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:41
msgid ""
"`true` or `false` literals, which are always `true`/`false` respectively"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:43
msgid "should be added to the explanation of the predicates."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:45
msgid ""
"`cfg(r#true)` and `cfg(r#false)` should continue to work as they did "
"previously (i.e. enabled when `--cfg true`/`--cfg false` are passed)."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:47
msgid ""
"`true` and `false` should be expected everywhere Configuration Predicates "
"are used, i.e."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:48
msgid "the `#[cfg(..)]` attribute"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:49
msgid "the `cfg!(..)` macro"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:50
msgid "the `#[cfg_attr(.., ..)]` attribute"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:52
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:55
msgid ""
"By making it more convenient, this may encourage unconditionally disabled "
"blocks of code being committed, which is undesirable."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:57
msgid "Rationale and alternatives"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:60
msgid ""
"This could instead be spelled as `cfg(disabled|enabled)`, or `cfg(none)` for "
"disabling code only. However, giving special meaning to a valid identifier "
"will change the meaning of existing code, requiring a new edition"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:61
msgid ""
"As the existing predicates evaluate to booleans, using boolean literals is "
"the most intuitive way to spell this"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:63
msgid "Prior art"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:66
msgid ""
"Many languages with conditional compilation constructs have a way to disable "
"a block entirely."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:68
msgid "C: `#if 0`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:69
msgid "C#: `#if false`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:70
msgid "Dlang: `version(none)`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:71
msgid "Haskell: `#if 0`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:73
msgid ""
"Searching for `cfg(false)` on [GitHub](https://github.com/search?"
"q=%23%5Bcfg%28false%29%5D+language%3ARust&type=code) reveals many examples "
"of projects (including Rust itself) using `cfg(FALSE)` as a way to get this "
"behavior - although this raises a `check-cfg` warning."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:75
msgid "Future possibilities"
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:78
msgid ""
"A future lint could suggest replacing constructs such as `cfg(any())` with "
"`cfg(false)`, and `cfg(all())` with `cfg(true)`."
msgstr ""

#: src/3695-cfg-boolean-literals.md:80
msgid ""
"The `check-cfg` lint could be with a special case for identifiers such as "
"`FALSE` and suggest `cfg(false)` instead."
msgstr ""
